main_definition: To move or proceed in a particular direction, especially forward.

meanings_and_examples.definition: Move from one place to another physically.
meanings_and_examples.example: I need to go to the grocery store to buy some milk.

meanings_and_examples.definition: Proceed with an activity or task.
meanings_and_examples.example: Let's start going through our project checklist now.

meanings_and_examples.definition: Start a new venture or initiative.
meanings_and_examples.example: The company decided to go into the renewable energy sector.

meanings_and_examples.definition: Prepare for an event or activity in advance.
meanings_and_examples.example: We need to go over our presentation one more time before the meeting.

meanings_and_examples.definition: Begin a new phase of life, often associated with graduating from school.
meanings_and_examples.example: After finishing high school, I went on to attend university.
My phone seems to go fine after the software update.

meanings_and_examples.definition: To leave a location and proceed elsewhere.
meanings_and_examples.example: I had to go home early because I wasn't feeling well.
